<TITLE> Sylhet mayor resigns party post </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sylhet, Aug 31 (bdnews24.com)  Sylhet mayor-elect Badruddin Ahmed Kamran quit his party post Sunday. The city's Awami League president, now under treatment at Sylhet Osmany Hospital, signed the resignation paper Sunday morning, said his wife Asma Kamran. She sent the resignation letter to party acting president Zillur Rahman. She also submitted the copies of the resignation letter to Sylhet city AL general secretary Misbahuddin Siraj and Sylhet additional divisional commissioner JN Biswas at around 12 noon. Misbahuddin Siraj told bdnews24.com: "I have received the copy of mayor Kamran's resignation letter this morning." The detained mayor-elect was released on parole on Aug 18 following the death of his mother; he fell sick after returning to Sylhet Central Jail that evening. He was admitted to Sylhet Osmany Hospital where he has been under treatment since. Four cases are now under trial against the re-elected Kamran. He is on bail in cases against for concealing wealth, violating emergency powers rules and kitchen market corruption. A case filed against him under the narcotics act has been stayed by the High Court. The newly elected mayors of Rajshahi, Sylhet, Khulna and Barisal and mayors and councillors of nine municipalities are scheduled to be sworn in by Sept 11. According to the new local government ordinance elected mayors and councillors must submit proof of their resignation from party posts to their divisional commissioner before taking their oaths. bdnews2
